[h1]ONI ONLINE 1.0.8[/h1]

Current Stage: v1.0.8

Run one shared Oxygen Not Included colony with friends. ONI ONLINE is an independent, unofficial fork with its own name, Workshop item, release line, and network protocol.

[h2]Multiplayer[/h2]

[list]
[*]Steam friends lobbies with invite and lobby-code joining
[*]Steam relay/NAT traversal with no port forwarding or LAN tunnel
[*]Optional direct LAN connections
[*]Shared colony controls, player cursors, chat, pings, and drawings
[*]Host-authoritative actions with automatic state repair
[*]Full snapshot join and reconnect recovery
[*]Large-save transfer over TCP with automatic UDP fallback
[/list]

[h2]Host-authoritative synchronization[/h2]

Shared colony mutations use one request path. A client submits an action request; the host validates the sender, session, target, permissions, domain rules, and revision; the host then executes the accepted action and broadcasts the resulting authoritative state. Clients do not treat local clicks as committed colony state. Duplicate, stale, and out-of-order updates are rejected, while generation-bound snapshots and replay restore joining or reconnecting clients.

[h2]Supported content[/h2]

The release supports the base game, Spaced Out!, Frosty Planet Pack, Bionic Booster Pack, Prehistoric Planet Pack, Neutronium Cosmetics Pack, and Aquatic Planet Pack.

Every player must use the same ONI ONLINE DLL SHA-256 and enable the same DLC set. A rejected client sees the specific DLL or DLC mismatch before world transfer. Other enabled Mods, load order, and configuration are not admission checks.

Steam multiplayer requires a separate Steam account for each running game instance. The host shares the lobby code or sends a Steam invite; SteamNetworkingSockets handles the Internet route.

[h2]Controls[/h2]

[list]
[*]Ctrl + right click: ping
[*]Ctrl + right drag: draw
[*]Ctrl + left click a drawing: delete it
[*]Shift + R: reset the chat window
[/list]

[h2]Source[/h2]

https://github.com/Ericbai06/Oxygen_Not_Included_Together

ONI ONLINE is based on the active, MIT-licensed ONI Together project:
https://github.com/Lyraedan/Oxygen_Not_Included_Together

Original project by Lyraedan (ItsLuke), Sgt_Imalas, and its contributors. ONI ONLINE does not replace or represent the upstream project.

[h2]Why a separate fork?[/h2]

Protocol 11 changes the network contract across request authority, transport, replay, reconnect, entity lifecycle, revision handling, DLC synchronization, and the integration-test harness. The changes are interdependent and are not wire-compatible with the upstream 0.7.x release line. Submitting the entire fork as one pull request would create a large, non-incremental review that mixes architectural decisions with individual fixes. Fixes that can be isolated from protocol 11 should still be proposed upstream as focused pull requests.

Licensed under MIT. Third-party notices are included with the Mod.
